'''2016年[[保守黨_(英國)|英國保守黨]]黨魁選舉'''（{{lang-en|Conservative Party leadership election, 2016}}）緣由於2016年6月23日舉行的[[2016年英國脫離歐盟公投|2016年英國脫離歐盟公投]]以「脫離歐盟」作結果，時任[[英國保守黨黨魁列表|黨魁]]及[[英國首相|英國首相]][[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]其後宣布於2016年10月（或更早，若新黨魁在一個較早的日期當選）辭職所引發<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36615028|title=Brexit: David Cameron to quit after UK votes to leave EU|date=24 June 2016|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2016-07-03|archive-date=2018-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118045301/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36615028|dead-url=no}}</ref>，選舉原定在2016年9月9日舉行<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36640889 |title=New Tory leader 'should be in place by 9 September' |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=28 June 2016 |website=BBC |publisher=BBC |access-date=29 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630044522/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36640889 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

由於保守黨現時是[[英國下議院|英國下議院]]的{{le|多數政府|Majority government|多數黨}}，因此獲勝者將幾乎肯定擔任首相<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36633595|title=Brexit: New PM 'should come from Leave camp'|publisher=BBC News|date=26 June 2016|accessdate=2016-07-03|archive-date=2016-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629180111/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36633595|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並出任此職至不遲於2020年5月7日舉行之下次大選，除非下議院在{{le|2011年國會固定任期法案|Fixed-term Parliaments Act 2011}}下投票通過決定提早解散國會或國會廢除上述法律<ref>{{cite web |title=Fixed-term Parliament Act 2011 (c. 14), section 2. |url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2011/14/section/2/enacted |website=Legislation.gov.uk |accessdate=25 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629072925/http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2011/14/section/2/enacted |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

大多數政治分析家對[[高文浩|高文浩]]撤回支持[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]參選保守黨黨魁，並在無任何事前通知前於6月30日提名自己出選而感到驚訝。隨後，於黨魁提名結束前幾分鐘，鲍里斯·约翰逊宣布不打算參選<ref>{{cite news |last=Hughes |first=Laura |date=30 June 2016 |title=Boris Johnson announces he will not run for Prime Minister as Michael Gove declares his bid after claiming his colleague 'cannot provide the leadership' |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/30/boris-johnson-and-theresa-may-go-head-to-head-in-conservative-le/ |newspaper=The Telegraph |location=London, UK |access-date=30 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630082803/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/30/boris-johnson-and-theresa-may-go-head-to-head-in-conservative-le/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，雖然他在多數政治分析中持領先地位<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/brexit-boris-johnson-1.3659425 |title=Boris Johnson, former London mayor, rules out bid to be next British PM |author=Thomson Reuters!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=30 June 2016 |website=CBC News |publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation |access-date=30 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-07-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160703064829/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/brexit-boris-johnson-1.3659425 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

